>You have to be careful with a tail to a stem which itself contains
>period(s). REXX will convert the stem name (all characters up to, and
>including, the first period) to upper case but will leave the
>tail (all characters following the first period) in its presented case.

Hmmm.. This is great information but you didn't answer the question.
At least it is not clear that you did.

YES, you can index a stem using a plain variable.  Otherwise, the stem
would be virtually useless.

     do i=0 to stema.0
	say stema.i
     end

This loop is done all the time.  However, you cannot index stema with
another stem variable.  You basically have to use a temporary variable.

    tmp = stemb.0
    say stema.tmp

 -Steve


